data.description: The 101. TRULY a 1 of 1!  - Welcome to a one-of-a-kind roundhouse, where classic charm meets modern luxury. In addition to its unique architecture, The 101 also features phenomenal outdoor living spaces, and a guest house. Located in the Open Sands subdivision of Panama City Beach, Florida! The Main house features 3-bedrooms and 2-bathrooms, was originally constructed in 1959 and was recently rejuvenated with modern materials and finishes while meticulously preserving the architectural essentials that define The 101. You will now find wood-like tile floors throughout, sliding glass doors with built-in blinds all around providing loads of natural light and access to the outdoors from every room. The Kitchen features as its centerpiece a large island with leathered marble countertop capable of accommodating seating for up to 8-guests. Other kitchen features include stainless steel appliances, shaker cabinets, subway tile backsplash, seamless sink and Corian countertops. The open concept to the cozy living room with built-in bar, wine fridge and built-in cabinets makes for an easy transition from one social setting to the next.The main house's bedrooms all have built-in custom closets with light fixtures. The primary bedroom suite swanks a glass enclosure sunroom and private bathroom equipped with a custom tiled rain shower and exterior door that provides access to a covered walkway connection leading to the guest house.The entire property is beautifully landscaped with a mature Magnolia tree and Palms. A stone pavers driveway with integrated lighting leads to the main house entrance and then continues down the side yard and wraps around to the backyard arriving at a large sitting area with built-in fireplace finished with a Breeo insert! Trex decking surrounds the other side of the main house and extends to the backyard as well, connecting the outdoor living spaces to both the main house and the guest house. There is even a private outdoor shower satisfying every requisite of even those with the most demanding of tastes.The guest house has 2-bedrooms, a bunk room that can easily accommodate 7-guests, plus a full bathroom and a small office. Open concept kitchenette, living and dining area. The laundry room located in the guest house connects to the main house through the covered walkway and has space for a large stackable washer and dryer and full-size refrigerator. There is also a utility sink, storage cabinets, a countertop for folding and a plumbed ice maker. In the front of the guest house there's 3 covered outdoor parking spaces, an enclosed workshop with secure parking for a motorcycle or golf cart and plenty of storage. This energy efficient house is powered by privately owned solar panels with power bills as low as $30/month. Behind the guest house there's a storage shed with separate storage for the metal hurricane protection shutters and a raised garden in addition to a Grapefruit tree, a Persian lime tree and a Meyer's lemon tree.The 101 is just a short golf cart ride to Beach access #51 right next to the fine dining of Runaway Island and around the corner from Autentika Mexican Grill. Find your perfect Florida life, living in this golf cart friendly neighborhood just 20-minutes from the ECP international airport and a stroll away from the white sugary sand and emerald waters of Panama City Beach, FL. TRIVIA: Did you know that the best hurricane resistant houses are roundhouses and that some of the earliest construction of roundhouses can be dated back to 3,000 B.C.? Also, some sources claim that roundhouses promote healthy living by design, and provide superior acoustics compared to their rectangular counterparts.STR not allowed in Open Sands, must be a minimum of 6-months.All information is deemed correct, buyers should verify if they are important.
